Sentencas: The electrochemical properties of mixed-conducting ceramic-ceramic (cer-cer) composites for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells (PC-SOFCs) based on La0.995Ca0.005NbO4-delta (LCN) have been investigated.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of composite cathodes for La0.995Ca0.005NbO4-δ-based proton conducting fuel cells

Sentencas: Different ratios of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-delta/La0.995Ca0.005NbO4-delta (LSM/LCN) composites have been tested as cathodes in symmetrical cells based on La0.995Ca0.005NbO4-delta dense electrolytes while two different electrode sintering temperatures (1050 and 1150 degrees C) have been studied.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of composite cathodes for La0.995Ca0.005NbO4-δ-based proton conducting fuel cells

Sentencas: Additionally, different LCN doped materials (Pr, Ce and Mn), which present a different conduction behavior, have been used as components in composite cathodes (mixtures of LSM/doped-LCN 50/50 vol.%).
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of composite cathodes for La0.995Ca0.005NbO4-δ-based proton conducting fuel cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy analysis has been carried out in the temperature range 700-900 degrees C under moist (2.5%) atmospheres.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of composite cathodes for La0.995Ca0.005NbO4-δ-based proton conducting fuel cells

Sentencas: Different oxygen partial pressures (pO(2)) have been employed in order to characterize the processes (surface reaction and charge transport) occurring at the composite electrode under oxidizing conditions.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of composite cathodes for La0.995Ca0.005NbO4-δ-based proton conducting fuel cells

Sentencas: The main outcome of the present study is that the mixture of LSM (electronic phase) and LCN (protonic phase) enables to decrease substantially the electrode polarization resistance.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of composite cathodes for La0.995Ca0.005NbO4-δ-based proton conducting fuel cells

Sentencas: This is ascribed to the increase in the three-phase-boundary length and therefore it allows electrochemical reactions to occur in a larger region (thickness) of the electrode.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of composite cathodes for La0.995Ca0.005NbO4-δ-based proton conducting fuel cells
